<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hostess" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hostess</orth> (having <emph>an</emph> before it as ind. art.: <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.253" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 253</bibl>; <emph>mine</emph> and <emph>thine</emph> as poss. pron.; only twice, or rather once, <cit><quote>my:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 45</bibl></cit>. 54) 1) a woman who entertains guests or strangers: <bibl n="shak. luc 1125" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.5.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 5, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.5.45" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 5, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.64" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.6.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 6, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.6.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 6, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.6.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 6, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mac 2.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.4.5" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 5</bibl>.<lb />2) a woman who keeps an inn: <cit><quote>the h. of the house,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 88.</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>ruminates like an h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.253" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 253</bibl></cit>. Vocative: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.305" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 305</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.68" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.68" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 68</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.68" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 68</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.68" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 68</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.86" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.86" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 86</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.86" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 86</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.86" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 86</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 86</bibl> (O. Edd. <emph>your h.,</emph> M. Edd. <emph>you, h.</emph>). <bibl n="shak. h5 2.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 62</bibl>. <cit><quote>my h. of the tavern,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 45</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 45</bibl> <cit><quote>mine h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 119</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.289" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 289</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.122" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 122</bibl>. <cit><quote>thine h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.122" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 122</bibl></cit> Jocularly: <cit><quote>my lady the h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.315" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 315</bibl></cit>.
